A recommendation from https://github.com/dotnet/aspnetcore/issues/30247

We believe we're incurring a significant cost by waiting for the main thread of VS (see here for additional analysis), with >25% of calls in the sample waiting >100ms just for the main thread.

@NTaylorMullen says this will be fixed by his refactor to avoid syncing, but that's a ways off. Another solution was to stop updating the buffers in this case and just send a didChange request to the language server, but that's a relatively big change in its own right that we might not want to make just to throw it away after Taylors refactor.

When you have one component inside another, you may see that a common, outer component is created before the inner. They have the same disposal order. However, if the Ctrl+F5 key combination is used, the disposal order is broken.
To illustrate this, use the following code:

```razor
@inherits DxAsyncDisposableComponent

@using System.Threading

<div>
    This is outer component
    <InnerComponent></InnerComponent>
</div>

@code {
    public OuterComponent()
    {
        System.Diagnostics.Debug.WriteLine("Outer component is created: " + this.GetHashCode());
    }
    protected override CancellationToken CancellationToken => new CancellationTokenSource().Token;

    protected override void Dispose()
    {
        System.Diagnostics.Debug.WriteLine("Outer component is disposed: " + this.GetHashCode());
    }
}
```

where InnerComponent can be defined in a similar manner:

```razor
@inherits DxAsyncDisposableComponent

@using System.Threading

<div>
    This is inner component
</div>

@code {
    public InnerComponent() {
        System.Diagnostics.Debug.WriteLine("Inner component is created: " + this.GetHashCode());
    }
    protected override CancellationToken CancellationToken => new CancellationTokenSource().Token;

    protected override void Dispose()
    {
        System.Diagnostics.Debug.WriteLine("Inner component is disposed: " + this.GetHashCode());
    }
}
```

Where DxAsyncDisposableComponent implements IAsyncDisposable:

```cs
public abstract class DxAsyncDisposableComponent : ComponentBase, IAsyncDisposable
    {
        bool disposed;
        protected bool Disposed => disposed;
        protected abstract CancellationToken CancellationToken { get; }
        async ValueTask IAsyncDisposable.DisposeAsync()
        {
            if (!disposed)
            {
                disposed = true;
                try
                {
                    var task = OnDisposeAsync();
                    Dispose();
                    await task;
                }
                catch (OperationCanceledException e)
                {
                    if (e.CancellationToken != CancellationToken)
                        throw;
                }
            }
        }

        protected abstract void Dispose();
        protected virtual ValueTask OnDisposeAsync() => default;
    }
```

